            style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class=""
            lang="EN-US">Long papers</span></i><span style="font-family:
          Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">: technical papers
          reporting original research or survey papers</span><span
          class="" lang="EN-US"><o:p class=""></o:p></span></li>
      <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; font-size:
        11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><i class=""><span
            style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class=""
            lang="EN-US">Short papers</span></i><span
          style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">:
          papers reporting promising work-in-progress, system
          descriptions, position papers on controversial issues, or
          survey papers</span><span class="" lang="EN-US"> </span><span
          style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">providing
          a synthesis of some current research trends</span><span
          class="" lang="EN-US"><o:p class=""></o:p></span></li>
      <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; font-size:
        11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><i class=""><span
            style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class=""
            lang="EN-US">Extended abstracts</span></i><span
          style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US"> of
          recently published work in a relevant journal or top-tier
          conference</span><span class="" lang="EN-US"><o:p class=""></o:p></span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="western" style="margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;
      font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
      margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial,
        sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">Accepted long and short
        papers will be published by Springer in the <a
          moz-do-not-send="true" href="http://www.springer.com/lncs"
          style="color: purple;" class="">Lecture Notes in Artificial
          Intelligence series</a>. Authors of an accepted long or short
        paper will be expected to sign copyright release forms, and one
        author is expected to give a presentation at the conference.
        Authors of accepted abstracts will be expected to present their
        work during the conference, but the extended abstracts will not
        be published in the LNCS/LNAI proceedings (they will be made
        available in a separate booklet).</span><o:p class=""></o:p></p>
    <p class="western" style="margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;
      font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
      margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial,
        sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">Regular research papers
        should be at most 14 pages (including references, figures and
        tables). Short papers should be at most 7 pages. Extended
        abstracts should be at most 2 pages and should reference the
        originally published work. </span><o:p class=""></o:p></p>
    <p class="western" style="margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;
      font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
      margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial,
        sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">Submissions must be formatted
        according to Springer's guidelines for LNCS authors, which can
        be found at</span><u class=""><span style="color: navy;"
          class=""><a moz-do-not-send="true"
            href="http://www.springer.de/comp/lncs/authors.html"
            style="color: purple;" class=""><span style="font-family:
              Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US"></span></a><a
            moz-do-not-send="true" class="moz-txt-link-freetext"
            href="http://www.springer.de/comp/lncs/authors.html"
            style="color: purple;"><a class="moz-txt-link-freetext" href="http://www.springer.de/comp/lncs/authors.html">http://www.springer.de/comp/lncs/authors.html</a></a></span></u><span
        style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">.
        Each paper is to be submitted electronically as a single PDF
        file through EasyChair at </span><u class=""><span
          style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: navy;" class=""
          lang="EN-US"><a class="moz-txt-link-freetext"
            href="https://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=sum2017"
            style="color: purple;">https://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=sum2017</a></span></u><span
        style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">.
        Papers not respecting the formatting instructions or page limits
        may be rejected without review.</span><o:p class=""></o:p></p>
    <p class="western" style="margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;
      font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
      margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial,
        sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">With the exception of
        extended abstracts, submissions must be unpublished and must not
        be under submission elsewhere. All submitted papers will be
        reviewed by the Program Committee on the basis of technical
        quality, relevance, significance, and clarity. </span><o:p
        class=""></o:p></p>
    <p class="western" style="margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;
      font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
      margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><b class=""><span style="font-family:
          Arial, sans-serif;" class="" lang="EN-US">Important dates</span></b><o:p
        class=""></o:p></p>
    <p class="western" style="margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;
      font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
